snippet.title: FULL HEARING: Rodrigo Duterte faces ICC pre-trial chamber | ABS-CBN News
snippet.description:
Former Philippine President Rodrigo Roa Duterte made his initial appearance before the International Criminal Court Pre-Trial Chamber 1 on Friday (March 14), two days after his high-profile arrest in relation to his administration's war on drugs.

00:00 Hearing starts; Presiding Juge Iulia Motoc welcomes attendees
01:35 Court officer calls the case
02:28 Prosecutor Karim Khan introduces prosecution team
02:56 Motoc explains video link or virtual attendance of Rodrigo Duterte
03:30 Salvador Medialdea introduces himself as the legal counsel of Duterte

03:43 Motoc introduces the pre-trial chamber, including Judge Reine Alapini-Gansou and Judge Socorro Flores Liera
04:37 Motoc asks Duterte to confirm his identity; Duterte provides his full name, birth date, and birth place
06:20 Motoc explains the scope of the first appearance hearing
09:10 Court officer reads the charges against Duterte
10:51 Motoc addresses Duterte, explains his rights as suspect for the ICC

13:34 Medialdea asks to present a manifestation; Motoc allows him
14:50 Medialdea presents his manifestation, calls Duterte’s arrest as “pure and simple kidnapping”
16:56 Medialdea brings up Duterte’s physical condition and medical issues, and limited time to confer with the former president
18:20 Medialdea repeats request to ICC to postpone pre-trial hearing
19:04 Motoc addresses Duterte’s health, details measures to accommodate his condition

20:18 Motoc cites registry’s report that indicates Duterte was informed of his rights and the contents of his warrant of arrest
21:10 Motoc emphasizes the purpose of the pre-trial hearing includes informing Duterte of his rights and charges against him
22:16 Motoc says court has decided a second time to not accept Medialdea’s request to postpone the hearing
22:52 Motoc moves on, announces date for the confirmation of charges hearing: September 23, 2025
23:45 Motoc explains next procedural steps

24:51 Motoc orders prosecution to start disclosure of basis of warrant of arrest
25:08 Motoc says a decision will also be made on the participation of victims in future proceedings
25:27 Duterte’s first attendance hearing ends

snippet.title: China Slams ICC Over Duterte Arrest Warrant, Warns Against ‘Double Standards’
snippet.description:
China Slams ICC Over Duterte Arrest Warrant, Warns Against ‘Double Standards’

China’s foreign ministry announced that it was closely monitoring the situation after the Philippines arrested its former president, Rodrigo Duterte. The arrest, which came on a warrant issued by the International Criminal Court, marks a significant development in the ongoing ICC investigation into alleged crimes against humanity. During a regular press briefing, Chinese spokesperson Mao Ning addressed the situation, responding to questions about Duterte’s arrest. Duterte, a former mayor and prosecutor who served as president of the Philippines from 2016 to 2022, was taken into custody early on Tuesday. This marks the biggest step yet in the ICC’s investigation into Duterte’s controversial anti-drug crackdown, which led to thousands of deaths and widespread international condemnation. After his arrest, Duterte was sent to The Hague, where he is expected to arrive on the morning of March 12. At 79 years old, Duterte could become the first Asian former head of state to stand trial at the International Criminal Court
